      • setHitbox

        void setHitbox(Hitbox value)
        Sets the hitbox of this entity. This can be used to change the apparent 'size' of the entity's click boundary. Changing this to a smaller box will result in the original area of the large box being a dead zone, where clicking does nothing. When changing to a larger box, the new area can only be interacted with by using the attack action.
        Hitboxes can be generated through the FakeEntityFactory interface. An instance of this factory should be obtained from the PacketEntityAPI root instance.
        Parameters:
        value - the new hitbox to use for this entity

      • checkIntersect

        boolean checkIntersect(org.bukkit.entity.Player target)
        Checks whether or not the Player provided is intersecting the fake entity. This is used by the PacketEntityAPI engine to allow for the clicking of fake entities. To override the function used to check this, see setCheckIntersect(BiFunction)
        Parameters:
        target - the player to test
        Returns:
        whether or not the player is intersecting the fake entity

      • setField

        void setField(String name,
              Object value)
        Sets a parameter that is used in the spawning of this object. For example:
        "art" - The Art that should be shown on a painting.
        "direction" - A BlockFace that provides the direction of a painting or item frame.
        "orbCount" - The integer number of experience that an orb is worth.
        "velocity" - The velocity to spawn the object with.
        "shooter" - The integer Entity ID of the person who fired this fake entity.
        "id" - The type ID of the falling block's appearance.
        "data" - The data value of the falling block's appearance.

        You can also store custom data in here.

        Parameters:
        name - a name of a parameter given above
        value - the value to set it to
